Instead of explicitly using the className prop, we can just do something like:
const { seed, size, ...rest } = this.props;
return (<img src="..." height={size} width={size} {...rest} />)

This pulls out seed and size from props and then groups any other props as rest. We pass this down the line so we don't need to worry about things like className, onClick, etc.

body:
Instead of explicitly using the `className` prop, we can just do something like:

```
const { seed, size, ...rest } = this.props;
return (<img src="..." height={size} width={size} {...rest} />)
```

This pulls out `seed` and `size` from props and then groups any other props as `rest`. We pass this down the line so we don't need to worry about things like `className`, `onClick`, etc.
